headline.main: CHANGES IN BALKANS HINTED BY GERMANS; Only Danube Issue Settled by Award to Hungary

lead_paragraph: BERLIN, Sept. 1--The Axis award in the dispute between Rumania and Hungary continues to occupy political commentators. While it is designated as an outstanding diplomatic achievement its deeper implications also are stressed in private conversations in authoritative quarters.
